Let a triangle have vertices at $O(0,0)$, $A(a,0)$, and $B(b, c)$ in the $(x,
y)$-plane.

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")

+ Find the coordinates of a point $P(x, y)$ in the exterior of $triangle O A B$
  satisfying $"area"(triangle O A P) = "area"(triangle O B P) = "area"(triangle A B P)$.
+ Find the coordinates of a point $Q(x, y)$ in the interior of $triangle O A B$
  satisfying $"area"(triangle O A Q) = "area"(triangle O B Q) = "area"(triangle A B Q)$.
